something good about him."

763
00:42:57.608 --> 00:42:58.742
Dead silence.

764
00:42:58.809 --> 00:43:00.277
Goes on for about a minute.
two minutes.

765
00:43:00.344 --> 00:43:02.246
Finally. a voice from the back:

766
00:43:02.313 --> 00:43:03.681
"His brother was worse."

767
00:43:18.796 --> 00:43:20.364
I'm walking out
with the provolone.

768
00:43:20.431 --> 00:43:23.734
And I think he thinks
I smell like that.

769
00:43:29.173 --> 00:43:31.041
This<i> Survivor</i> show.

770
00:43:31.108 --> 00:43:33.077
somebody should
find the winner.

771
00:43:33.143 --> 00:43:35.112
stick a pistol
in the face. and say.

772
00:43:35.179 --> 00:43:36.580
"You not gonna survive this

773
00:43:36.647 --> 00:43:40.117
unless you give me 25% of that
fucking million dollars."

774
00:43:41.352 --> 00:43:42.519
<i>That's not bad.</i>

775
00:43:42.586 --> 00:43:43.921
<i>We could find out
where they live.</i>

776
00:43:43.988 --> 00:43:46.190
"See how good you survive
this.<i> pezzo di merda."</i>

777
00:43:47.992 --> 00:43:52.262
Everyone. please.
may I have your attention?

778
00:43:52.329 --> 00:43:54.865
At this time. we would
like to ask you all

779
00:43:54.932 --> 00:43:56.800
to join us in the great room.

780
00:43:56.867 --> 00:44:00.104
Form a circle. sit anywhere.
The floor. whatever.

781
00:44:00.170 --> 00:44:02.973
Get comfortable.
so that we can all be together

782
00:44:03.040 --> 00:44:06.710
and share a remembrance
or a feeling

783
00:44:06.777 --> 00:44:08.846
about the woman who has
brought us all here today.

784
00:44:08.912 --> 00:44:10.080
Goddamn it.

785
00:44:10.147 --> 00:44:11.782
<i>Please. everyone join us.</i>

786
00:44:13.183 --> 00:44:15.919
Paulie Gualtieri.
join us. please?

787
00:44:20.024 --> 00:44:21.258
Thank you.

788
00:44:24.862 --> 00:44:27.164
What the fuck
did I say. hmm?

789
00:44:29.166 --> 00:44:31.935
If you'd rather. I can invite
them all back to her place.

790
00:44:33.003 --> 00:44:34.738
Janice. what are you doing?

791
00:44:34.805 --> 00:44:36.206
Very good.

792
00:44:36.273 --> 00:44:38.776
We could all take a break
from eating for five minutes.

793
00:44:38.842 --> 00:44:40.077
It won't kill us.

794
00:44:42.112 --> 00:44:43.447
Most of you will
probably remember

795
00:44:43.514 --> 00:44:45.983
that this was her
favorite song.

796
00:44:47.684 --> 00:44:50.254
I thought it might
help us get rolling.

797
00:44:58.896 --> 00:45:03.200
<i>♪ If I loved you ♪</i>

798
00:45:03.267 --> 00:45:07.504
<i>♪ Time and again
I would try to say ♪</i>

799
00:45:07.571 --> 00:45:11.175
<i>♪ All I'd want you ♪</i>

800
00:45:11.241 --> 00:45:14.044
<i>♪ To know ♪</i>

801
00:45:16.580 --> 00:45:20.451
<i>♪ If I loved you ♪</i>

802
00:45:20.517 --> 00:45:24.822
<i>♪ Words wouldn't come
In an easy way ♪</i>

803
00:45:24.888 --> 00:45:28.092
<i>♪ Round in circles ♪</i>

804
00:45:28.158 --> 00:45:30.928
<i>♪ I'd go ♪</i>

805
00:45:33.831 --> 00:45:36.133
<i>♪ Longing to tell you ♪</i>

806
00:45:36.200 --> 00:45:37.768
<i>♪ But afraid... ♪</i>

807
00:45:51.148 --> 00:45:52.916
Herman? Rabkin?

808
00:45:59.189 --> 00:46:01.525
You two went back.
almost to the pyramids.

809
00:46:04.061 --> 00:46:05.429
I...

810
00:46:06.530 --> 00:46:09.066
I guess what struck me
most was...

811
