You just did.

840
00:48:33.110 --> 00:48:34.645
Wrap it up. Janice.

841
00:48:43.954 --> 00:48:45.789
I hear she didn't suffer.

842
00:48:47.157 --> 00:48:49.393
For that.
we can be grateful.

843
00:48:50.727 --> 00:48:52.229
<i>Thank you.</i>

844
00:48:55.932 --> 00:48:57.200
<i>They say...</i>

845
00:48:58.468 --> 00:49:01.938
there's no two people
on earth exactly the same.

846
00:49:02.939 --> 00:49:04.207
<i>No two faces.</i>

847
00:49:04.274 --> 00:49:07.110
No two sets
of fingerprints.

848
00:49:08.612 --> 00:49:09.913
But do they know that
for sure?

849
00:49:09.980 --> 00:49:13.950
'Cause they would have
to get everybody together

850
00:49:14.017 --> 00:49:17.054
in one huge space.

851
00:49:17.120 --> 00:49:20.757
And obviously. that's not
possible. even with computers.

852
00:49:22.059 --> 00:49:23.360
Not only that.

853
00:49:23.427 --> 00:49:26.263
they'd have to get
all the people who ever lived.

854
00:49:26.330 --> 00:49:27.698
<i>not just the ones now.</i>

855
00:49:27.764 --> 00:49:29.733
<i>So they got no proof.</i>

856
00:49:29.800 --> 00:49:31.168
<i>They got nothing.</i>

857
00:49:44.047 --> 00:49:45.349
Hey.

858
00:49:50.420 --> 00:49:52.989
- So. Ton'. she's dead.
- What?

859
00:49:56.360 --> 00:49:58.528
I guess our little secret...

860
00:50:00.564 --> 00:50:01.798
dies with her.

861
00:50:16.480 --> 00:50:17.647
Hey. pick that up!

862
00:50:18.982 --> 00:50:20.684
What am I doing out here?

863
00:50:21.852 --> 00:50:24.688
Everybody's in there
